Somehow, you find yourself in a dim and smoky room with no entrance, exit or windows, without knowing how

wood table. Surprisingly, you find the same type of hat in your very own hand when you look down.
   You are invited to join in, but not knowing the manner of the game or its rules, you decline, and receive 
a few disparaging looks because of your decision. The group of men shrug-off your refusal and continue 
playing regardless, and largely ignore you.
   As you watch and the game proceeds, you notice that the point seems to be to get as many hats as possible.
How many? You don't know, but more is surely better - if judging by the looks on everyone's faces whenever 
anyone wins a new Chinese hat is anything to go by. You also notice that the hats have a rather strange 
property, they can change size so they can slot inside each other perfectly, no matter how many there are.
You've never seen a hat like that before you admit to yourself, as you stroke your chin.
After a while, you begin to feel a bit bored by just watching the game, and there's nowhere else to go or be 
that you can think of. You can scarcely remember if there ever even had been. With the encouragement and

total of eight hats to begin playing with, including your own hat.
